craterdog.collections.interfaces

Interface Iteratable<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - The type of element managed by the collection.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Composite, java.lang.Iterable<E>, Sequential<E>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Accessible<E>, Associative<K,V>, FIFO<E>, Indexed<E>, LIFO<E>, Ordered<E>, Sortable<E>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Bag, Collection, Dictionary, List, Map, OrderedCollection, Queue, Set, SortableCollection, Stack

    public interface Iteratable<E>
extends Sequential<E>, Composite
    This interface defines the methods that must be implemented by each collection whose elements can be iterated over.
    Author:
    Derk Norton
